            <fr:title text="Correspondence between matrices and finite relations">Correspondence between <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> and finite <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link></fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>884</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IY</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IY.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The matrix associated to a finite relation">The <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link> associated to a finite <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link>; for any semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, we may form the <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S{R}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},j\in {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}} =
 \begin {cases}
   1&\text {if } i\mathrel {R}j
   \\
   0&\text {otherwise}
 \end {cases}
]]></fr:tex>
                <fr:p>We have defined a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} \to  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>885</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IZ</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IZ.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The relation associated to a matrix">The <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to a <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> over a semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. We define the <fr:em><fr:strong><fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> below:</fr:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
 \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M} &\colon  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}
 \\
 i\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M}\right )\mathclose {}}} j &\Longleftrightarrow  M_{i,j} = 1
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
                <fr:p>We have defined a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>887</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00J0</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00J0.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="A retraction from matrices to finite relations">A retraction from <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> to finite <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The <fr:link href="jms-00IY.xml" title="The matrix associated to a finite relation" addr="jms-00IY" type="local">associated matrix</fr:link> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} \to  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a section of the <fr:link href="jms-00IZ.xml" title="The relation associated to a matrix" addr="jms-00IZ" type="local">associated relation</fr:link> function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for any semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>886</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/511</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-511.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We must check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\circ \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S = \mathsf {id}_{\mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex>. Fixing a relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we compute:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   i\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_SR\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}} j
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_SR\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = 1
   \\
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   i\mathrel {R}j
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>The other composite <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S\circ  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is not in general the identity function, but is (necessarily) an <fr:em>idempotent</fr:em> on the set of matrices over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. We will see that this idempotent, in some sense, measures the degree to which the base semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is not boolean.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>889</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IX</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>jms-00IX.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Finite relations as matrices over the booleans">Finite <fr:link href="jms-00IR.xml" title="Relations and matrices" addr="jms-00IR" type="local">relations</fr:link> as <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> over the booleans</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The idempotent <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}\circ  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B}\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> is in fact the identity function on matrices over the boolean semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>888</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/539</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-539.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We fix a matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j}
   &=
   \begin {cases}
   1 &\text {if } i \mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}} j\\
   0 &\text {otherwise}
   \end {cases}
   \\
   &=
   \begin {cases}
   1 &\text {if } M_{i,j} = 1\\
   0 &\text {otherwise}
   \end {cases}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex> is the boolean semiring, any scalar <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex> is either <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we conclude:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = M_{i,j}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>Thus we conclude that an <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrix</html:span> over the booleans is the same thing as a relation from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
