            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>4103</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IS</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00IS.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Matrix over a semiring">Matrix over a semiring</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>For natural numbers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, an <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrix</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> over a semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (S,0,\oplus ,1,\odot \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is given by entries <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_{i,j}\in  S]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrices</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>4104</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00I7</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00I7.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Relation">Relation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>(binary) relation</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> from a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\subseteq  A\times  B]]></fr:tex>. We shall typically write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {R}b]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (a,b\right )\mathclose {}}\in  R]]></fr:tex>. More generally, a <fr:em><fr:strong>relation between multiple sets</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A_i\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a subset of the cartesian product <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\prod _{i\in  I} A_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>4105</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IY</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00IY.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The matrix associated to a finite relation">The <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link> associated to a finite <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link>; for any semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, we may form the <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> as follows:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S{R}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},j\in {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}} =
 \begin {cases}
   1&\text {if } i\mathrel {R}j
   \\
   0&\text {otherwise}
 \end {cases}
]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>We have defined a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} \to  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>4106</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IZ</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00IZ.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The relation associated to a matrix">The <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to a <fr:link href="jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (n\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-<fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> over a semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. We define the <fr:em><fr:strong><fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> below:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
 \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M} &\colon  {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}
 \\
 i\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S{M}\right )\mathclose {}}} j &\Longleftrightarrow  M_{i,j} = 1
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
            <fr:p>We have defined a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_S\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}},{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
